guardians.model.entities

Class Doctor

  • java.lang.Object
    • guardians.model.entities.Doctor

  • @Entity
public class Doctor
extends java.lang.Object
    This Entity represents the information of a Doctor that will be stored in the database Doctors have some periodic shifts. This is, if some Doctors have a shift today, after a certain number of days, they will have another one. This kind of shifts will be referred to as "cycle-shift", and should not be confused with regular shifts. A "regular shift", or "shift" in short, refers to the shifts that will vary from month to month and that do not occur periodically. This kind of shifts are scheduled from startDate
    Author:
    miggoncan
